SUMMARY:Benefit show 15$ for comunities of Masafer Yatta\, Palestine
LOCATION:1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)
DESCRIPTION:2026-04-18 19:30:00\n\n1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)\n\nhttp
 s://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797\n\nALL EYES ON MASAFER YATTA\nMa
 safer Yatta is a collection of 19 villages in the South Hebron Hills of th
 e West Bank\, Palestine. This rural region is considered "Area C"\, which 
 are territories of the West Bank that are under complete control of the Is
 raeli government and it's occupation force and make up more than 60% of th
 e West Bank. While Palestinians in these areas are subjected to millitary 
 checkpoints which they cant cross without special permits\, the Israeli ap
 artheid law allows Israeli citizens to have complete freedom of movement t
 hrough these areas\, areas that are used as a large and important part in 
 the zionist settler project of greater Israel. The zionist regime tactical
 ly places violent settlers on hills over the Palestinian villages. Protect
 ed by the law\, the army and the police\, the settlers use physical and ps
 ychological terror on the Palestinians with the goal of running them out o
 f their villages and taking over. This system of violence and intimidation
  backed up by the law creates a living environment of constant danger and 
 fear\, and we see the situation escalating day by day - communites attacke
 d\, villages burnt and destroyed and Palestinians having everything taken 
 away from them while the settlers are getting more and more power. Masafer
  Yatta is an area which is extremely prone to attacks\, where not a day go
 es by peacefully. Any attempt by the Palestinians to resist their living b
 eing taken away from them can result in arrests\, violence or worse - loss
  of lives.\nOn April 11th\, people in many different cities across differe
 nt continents are standing up\, raising their voices and organizing\, both
  to collect money for those communites so they can hopefully recover and r
 ebuild what is taken from them by the israeli occupation\, as well as to s
 how solidarity with the Palestinians living under the occupation of the vi
 olent zionist regime - and to state we will keep fighting until its fall.\
 nThe Montreal show is gonna happen on April 18th as there is already a ben
 efit gig for Noise Not Borders on April 11th\, but we will have a donation
  stand at that gig as well so come see us!\nDoors : 7:30 pm\nShow : 8:30 p
 m\nSynaptic Isolation Syndrome - Fast Crust\, Montreal\nVarices - Grindcor
 e\, Sherbrooke\nMigración Animal - Crust Punk\, Montreal\nAt B7 (1900 rue
  Le Ber)\n15$ at the door\nAll ages\nKeep resisting\nKeep fighting\nLong l
 ive Palestine\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-73
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260401T040341
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T140000
SUMMARY:SLAM/MATU - Cercle de locataires
LOCATION:1800 Letourneux (métro Pie-IX)
DESCRIPTION:2026-04-19 12:00:00\n\n1800 Letourneux (métro Pie-IX)\n\nhttp
 s://www.openstreetmap.org/way/363150208\n\nLocataires d'Hochelaga\, rejoig
 nez-nous tous les dimanches pour discuter de l'augmentation de votre loyer
  et de la lutte collective contre les loyers dans notre quartier. N'accept
 ez rien\, même si ça semble petit\, avant d'en parler avec votre section
  locale du syndicat des locataires ! Et même là\, refusez votre augmenta
 tion ! On doit résister à chaque augmentation de loyer et profiter de ce
 s moments pour renforcer notre solidarité\, notre autodéfense\, notre r
 ésistance et notre organisation.\nChaque dimanche\, nous nous réunirons 
 en cercle de locataires. Nous écouterons les problèmes de chacun et prop
 oserons collectivement des suggestions pour aller de l'avant. Nous nous co
 ncentrerons sur la manière dont le groupe peut aider à faire pression su
 r votre propriétaire pour qu'il réduise votre augmentation de loyer\, qu
 e ce soit par des piquetages\, des visites collectives à son bureau ou à
  son domicile\, des affiches ou des lettres. Nous discuterons également d
 es campagnes spécifiques déjà en cours contre les propriétaires du qua
 rtier. À 14 h\, nous partirons distribuer des tracts et pour faire du por
 te-à-porte afin d'entrer en contact avec les locataires de certains des p
 lus grands propriétaires d'Hochelaga que nous ciblons.\nRésistons à la 
 gentrification et au contrôle capitaliste de notre quartier ! Exproprions
  nos immeubles\, libérons nos rues\, et luttons pour une commune d'Hochel
 aga !\n#tenantsunion #syndicatdeslocataires #housingcrisis #crisedelogemen
 t #anarchist #anticapitalist #abolishrent #Montreal #Hochelaga
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/363150208
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-74
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260401T040341
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T170000
SUMMARY:Violet Hour Book Club: "Starry Night"
LOCATION:6450 avenue Christophe-Colomb
DESCRIPTION:2026-04-19 15:00:00\n\n6450 avenue Christophe-Colomb\n\nhttps:
 //www.openstreetmap.org/way/1080082859\n\nJoin us for the next meeting of 
 the Violet Hour Book Club\, a reading group devoted to classic and contemp
 orary works of LGBTQ literature. The book we will be discussing is Starry 
 Starry Night (2025) by Shani Mootoo.\nToustes sont invités·es au Violet 
 Hour Book Club\, et chacun.e est bienvenu.e à partager ses pensées sur l
 e livre en anglais ou en français.\nWe will be meeting at Espace des Poss
 ibles Petite-Patrie (1052 Beaubien Street East\, Beaubien Metro). L’Espa
 ce des Possibles a comme mission d’offrir un lieu d’entraide\, d’app
 rentissages et d’implication dédié à la transition sociale et écolog
 ique (la transition socio-écologique).\nThe space is given to us for free
 \, but VHBC participants are welcome to make voluntary contributions to he
 lp support our mandate to create LGBTQ literary events for Montrealers.\nA
  reminder: All VHBC titles are available at Librairie Paragraphe Bookstore
  (2220\, McGill College Ave) at 15% off and at Librairie Pulp Books &amp\;
  Cafe (3952 Wellington St.) at 10% off.\nABOUT THE BOOK ///\nIn Starry Sta
 rry Night\, Mootoo gives us the singular voice of Anju Ghoshal\, a young g
 irl living in 1960s Trinidad. Through Anju’s innocent and clear-eyed obs
 ervations\, the reader becomes both a witness to and a participant in her 
 negotiations of an unexpectedly new and complex life\, spanning from the a
 ges of four to twelve.\nSet against the backdrop of a politically exciting
  time in Trinidad’s history\, just before and after it gained independen
 ce\, we meet Anju’s beloved Ma and Pa and her socially advancing family.
  While preoccupied with their own dramas\, the adults around her often fai
 l to recognize the needs of the children who depend on them.\nBeautifully 
 crafted and rich with sumptuous detail\, this unique narrative coalesces i
 nto a portrait of a child who\, despite her privileged appearance\, must u
 ltimately fend for herself because her safety depends on it.\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/1080082859
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
